# Walkthrough: AI Summary Pipeline Refactoring

## Summary

Refactored the AI Minutes of Meeting (MoM) pipeline from a sequential 4-agent architecture (sending the same transcript through Topic → Discussion → Action → Synthesis agents) to a **production-grade asynchronous parallel single-extraction architecture** that processes each transcript chunk exactly once.

## Architecture: Before vs After

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph Before ["Old: Sequential 4-Agent Pipeline"]
        direction TB
        A1["Agent 1: Topic Segmentation<br/>N chunks × 1 call"] --> A2["Agent 2: Discussion + Action<br/>N chunks × 1 call"]
        A2 --> A3["Agent 3: Final Synthesis<br/>1 call"]
        A3 --> A4["Agent 4: Validation<br/>1 call"]
    end

    subgraph After ["New: Async Parallel Pipeline"]
        direction TB
        S1["Stage 1: Transcript Cleaner<br/>(pure Python)"] --> S2["Stage 2: Smart Chunking<br/>(pure Python)"]
        S2 --> S3["Stage 3: Parallel Extraction<br/>(asyncio + semaphore, 1 call/chunk)"]
        S3 --> S4["Stage 4: Incremental Merge<br/>(pure Python)"]
        S4 --> S5["Stage 5: Final Synthesis<br/>(1 LLM call)"]
        S5 --> S6["Stage 6: Validation<br/>(never blocks)"]
    end
```

### API Call Reduction

| Scenario (15 chunks) | Old Pipeline | New Pipeline | Reduction |
|---|---|---|---|
| Agent calls per chunk | 2 (Topic + Discussion) | 1 (Extraction) | **50%** |
| Total chunk calls | 30 | 15 | **50%** |
| Synthesis calls | 1 | 1 | Same |
| Validation calls | 1 | 0 (local) | **100%** |
| **Total LLM calls** | **32** | **16** | **50%** |
| With retries (est.) | 50-80+ | 16-20 | **~70-75%** |

## Files Modified

### [settings.py](file:///c:/Users/Vaps/PycharmProjects/AIMOM/config/settings.py)
Added new configuration settings:
- `MAX_CONCURRENT_EXTRACTIONS` — bounded async concurrency (default: 3)
- `EXTRACTION_MODEL` / `SYNTHESIS_MODEL` — model assignments
- `EXTRACTION_MAX_TOKENS` / `SYNTHESIS_MAX_TOKENS` — compact output budgets
- `PROVIDER_COOLDOWN_SECONDS` — rate-limit cooldown period
- `PROMPT_VERSION` — checkpoint invalidation tag
- `CHECKPOINT_DIR` — checkpoint storage path

### [provider_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/Vaps/PycharmProjects/AIMOM/ai/providers/provider_manager.py)
Refactored from fixed primary/fallback to **dynamic health-based provider scheduling**:
- `_rank_providers()` — orders providers by health status and average latency
- `_is_in_cooldown()` / `_cooldown_remaining()` — prevents hammering rate-limited providers
- `_record_success()` — tracks exponential moving average latency
- `_record_failure(enter_cooldown=True)` — triggers cooldown on 429 errors
- `execute()` — iterates ranked providers with automatic skip for cooled-down ones

### [checkpoint_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/Vaps/PycharmProjects/AIMOM/ai/stages/checkpoint_manager.py) `[NEW]`
- SHA-256 content-hash based chunk identification
- Rich metadata: provider, model, prompt version, retry count, timestamp, token usage
- Automatic invalidation when `PROMPT_VERSION` changes
- `load_all_completed()` for bulk resume detection
- `cleanup()` on successful pipeline completion

### [merge_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/Vaps/PycharmProjects/AIMOM/ai/stages/merge_engine.py) `[NEW]`
- Incremental `add_chunk()` / `finalize()` pattern
- Advanced normalization: names (title-case), dates, priorities (High/Medium/Low)
- SequenceMatcher-based deduplication for topics, discussions, and action items
- Missing-field validation with fallback defaults
- Chronological ordering by chunk index

### [six_agent_pipeline.py](file:///c:/Users/Vaps/PycharmProjects/AIMOM/ai/pipeline/six_agent_pipeline.py)
Complete rewrite as `SingleExtractionPipeline`:
- `asyncio.Semaphore`-bounded parallel extraction
- One compact LLM call per chunk (structured JSON output)
- `ThreadPoolExecutor` bridges sync ProviderManager with async workers
- Final synthesis receives **only merged JSON** (not raw transcript)
- `FourAgentPipeline = SingleExtractionPipeline` alias for backward compatibility

### [manager.py](file:///c:/Users/Vaps/PycharmProjects/AIMOM/ai/pipeline/manager.py)
- Updated imports and docstrings to reference `SingleExtractionPipeline`
- Public API (`analyze_meeting`, `translate_to_english`) **unchanged**

